{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1268,"text":"In the northwest corner\nof the United States,"},{"time":4853,"text":"right up near the Canadian border,"},{"time":7727,"text":"there's a little town\ncalled Libby, Montana,"},{"time":11553,"text":"and it's surrounded\nby pine trees and lakes"},{"time":16038,"text":"and just amazing wildlife"},{"time":20761,"text":"and these enormous trees\nthat scream up into the sky."},{"time":26099,"text":"And in there is a little town\ncalled Libby,"},{"time":29618,"text":"which I visited, which feels\nkind of lonely,"},{"time":33963,"text":"a little isolated."},{"time":36360,"text":"And in Libby, Montana,\nthere's a rather unusual woman"},{"time":40012,"text":"named Gayla Benefield."},{"time":42039,"text":"She always felt a little bit\nof an outsider,"},{"time":44402,"text":"although she's been there\nalmost all her life,"},{"time":46966,"text":"a woman of Russian extraction."},{"time":49414,"text":"She told me when she went to school,"},{"time":51153,"text":"she was the only girl who ever chose"},{"time":52926,"text":"to do mechanical drawing."},{"time":56174,"text":"Later in life, she got\na job going house to house"},{"time":60072,"text":"reading utility meters -- gas\nmeters, electricity meters."},{"time":64182,"text":"And she was doing the work\nin the middle of the day,"},{"time":67182,"text":"and one thing particularly\ncaught her notice, which was,"},{"time":70609,"text":"in the middle of the day\nshe met a lot of men"},{"time":74715,"text":"who were at home, middle\naged, late middle aged,"},{"time":79105,"text":"and a lot of them seemed\nto be on oxygen tanks."},{"time":84548,"text":"It struck her as strange."},{"time":87311,"text":"Then, a few years later, her\nfather died at the age of 59,"},{"time":90922,"text":"five days before he was due\nto receive his pension."},{"time":94852,"text":"He'd been a miner."},{"time":95940,"text":"She thought he must just have\nbeen worn out by the work."},{"time":101382,"text":"But then a few years\nlater, her mother died,"},{"time":105114,"text":"and that seemed stranger still,"},{"time":108131,"text":"because her mother came\nfrom a long line of people"},{"time":110965,"text":"who just seemed to live forever."},{"time":114826,"text":"In fact, Gayla's uncle\nis still alive to this day,"},{"time":118395,"text":"and learning how to waltz."},{"time":120569,"text":"It didn't make sense that Gayla's mother"},{"time":124004,"text":"should die so young."},{"time":126458,"text":"It was an anomaly, and she kept\npuzzling over anomalies."},{"time":130702,"text":"And as she did, other ones came to mind."},{"time":132758,"text":"She remembered, for example,"},{"time":134486,"text":"when her mother had broken a leg\nand went into the hospital,"},{"time":137585,"text":"and she had a lot of x-rays,"},{"time":139360,"text":"and two of them were leg\nx-rays, which made sense,"},{"time":142315,"text":"but six of them were chest\nx-rays, which didn't."},{"time":147125,"text":"She puzzled and puzzled over every piece"},{"time":150107,"text":"of her life and her parents' life,"},{"time":152483,"text":"trying to understand what she was seeing."},{"time":156484,"text":"She thought about her town."},{"time":158195,"text":"The town had a vermiculite mine in it."},{"time":161183,"text":"Vermiculite was used\nfor soil conditioners,"},{"time":164016,"text":"to make plants grow faster and better."},{"time":167296,"text":"Vermiculite was used to insulate lofts,"},{"time":170354,"text":"huge amounts of it put under the roof"},{"time":173001,"text":"to keep houses warm\nduring the long Montana winters."},{"time":176852,"text":"Vermiculite was in the playground."},{"time":179219,"text":"It was in the football ground."},{"time":180672,"text":"It was in the skating rink."},{"time":183105,"text":"What she didn't learn until she started\nworking this problem"},{"time":186934,"text":"is vermiculite is a very\ntoxic form of asbestos."},{"time":194019,"text":"When she figured out the puzzle,"},{"time":195798,"text":"she started telling everyone she could"},{"time":198704,"text":"what had happened, what had\nbeen done to her parents"},{"time":201371,"text":"and to the people\nthat she saw on oxygen tanks"},{"time":204441,"text":"at home in the afternoons."},{"time":207602,"text":"But she was really amazed."},{"time":209003,"text":"She thought, when everybody knows,\nthey'll want to do something,"},{"time":212075,"text":"but actually nobody wanted to know."},{"time":214297,"text":"In fact, she became so annoying"},{"time":216412,"text":"as she kept insisting\non telling this story"},{"time":218849,"text":"to her neighbors, to her friends,\nto other people in the community,"},{"time":222064,"text":"that eventually a bunch\nof them got together"},{"time":224184,"text":"and they made a bumper sticker,"},{"time":225692,"text":"which they proudly displayed\non their cars, which said,"},{"time":228960,"text":"\"Yes, I'm from Libby, Montana,"},{"time":231106,"text":"and no, I don't have asbestosis.\""},{"time":236646,"text":"But Gayla didn't stop.\nShe kept doing research."},{"time":240026,"text":"The advent of the Internet\ndefinitely helped her."},{"time":243217,"text":"She talked to anybody she could."},{"time":245237,"text":"She argued and argued,\nand finally she struck lucky"},{"time":248512,"text":"when a researcher came through town"},{"time":250712,"text":"studying the history of mines in the area,"},{"time":253146,"text":"and she told him her story,\nand at first, of course,"},{"time":256288,"text":"like everyone, he didn't believe her,"},{"time":258559,"text":"but he went back to Seattle\nand he did his own research"},{"time":261202,"text":"and he realized that she was right."},{"time":265362,"text":"So now she had an ally."},{"time":269424,"text":"Nevertheless, people still\ndidn't want to know."},{"time":272014,"text":"They said things like, \"Well,\nif it were really dangerous,"},{"time":275738,"text":"someone would have told us.\""},{"time":278771,"text":"\"If that's really why everyone was dying,"},{"time":281793,"text":"the doctors would have told us.\""},{"time":286369,"text":"Some of the guys used\nto very heavy jobs said,"},{"time":289745,"text":"\"I don't want to be a victim."},{"time":291556,"text":"I can't possibly be a victim, and anyway,"},{"time":293574,"text":"every industry has its accidents.\""},{"time":300507,"text":"But still Gayla went on,\nand finally she succeeded"},{"time":304313,"text":"in getting a federal\nagency to come to town"},{"time":306925,"text":"and to screen the inhabitants\nof the town --"},{"time":311213,"text":"15,000 people -- and what they discovered"},{"time":315941,"text":"was that the town had a mortality rate"},{"time":319360,"text":"80 times higher than anywhere\nin the United States."},{"time":325418,"text":"That was in 2002, and even at that moment,"},{"time":329434,"text":"no one raised their hand to say, \"Gayla,"},{"time":333124,"text":"look in the playground where\nyour grandchildren are playing."},{"time":337439,"text":"It's lined with vermiculite.\""},{"time":342143,"text":"This wasn't ignorance."},{"time":345210,"text":"It was willful blindness."},{"time":347979,"text":"Willful blindness is a legal\nconcept which means,"},{"time":351458,"text":"if there's information that you\ncould know and you should know"},{"time":354435,"text":"but you somehow manage not to know,"},{"time":357862,"text":"the law deems that you're willfully blind."},{"time":360608,"text":"You have chosen not to know."},{"time":364383,"text":"There's a lot of willful\nblindness around these days."},{"time":368782,"text":"You can see willful blindness in banks,"},{"time":371633,"text":"when thousands of people\nsold mortgages to people"},{"time":374690,"text":"who couldn't afford them."},{"time":376398,"text":"You could see them in banks"},{"time":378056,"text":"when interest rates were manipulated"},{"time":380220,"text":"and everyone around knew\nwhat was going on,"},{"time":382632,"text":"but everyone studiously ignored it."},{"time":385806,"text":"You can see willful blindness\nin the Catholic Church,"},{"time":389230,"text":"where decades of child abuse went ignored."},{"time":393851,"text":"You could see willful blindness"},{"time":396146,"text":"in the run-up to the Iraq War."},{"time":400657,"text":"Willful blindness exists\non epic scales like those,"},{"time":404296,"text":"and it also exists on very small scales,"},{"time":407191,"text":"in people's families,\nin people's homes and communities,"},{"time":411119,"text":"and particularly in organizations\nand institutions."},{"time":416597,"text":"Companies that have been studied\nfor willful blindness"},{"time":420839,"text":"can be asked questions like,"},{"time":423122,"text":"\"Are there issues at work"},{"time":425948,"text":"that people are afraid to raise?\""},{"time":429378,"text":"And when academics have\ndone studies like this"},{"time":431593,"text":"of corporations in the United States,"},{"time":433890,"text":"what they find is 85\npercent of people say yes."},{"time":439138,"text":"Eighty-five percent of people\nknow there's a problem,"},{"time":442146,"text":"but they won't say anything."},{"time":444221,"text":"And when I duplicated\nthe research in Europe,"},{"time":447608,"text":"asking all the same questions,"},{"time":450270,"text":"I found exactly the same number."},{"time":453360,"text":"Eighty-five percent.\nThat's a lot of silence."},{"time":457411,"text":"It's a lot of blindness."},{"time":459493,"text":"And what's really interesting is that when\nI go to companies in Switzerland,"},{"time":463137,"text":"they tell me, \"This\nis a uniquely Swiss problem.\""},{"time":466555,"text":"And when I go to Germany, they say,\n\"Oh yes, this is the German disease.\""},{"time":470755,"text":"And when I go to companies\nin England, they say,"},{"time":473065,"text":"\"Oh, yeah, the British\nare really bad at this.\""},{"time":476804,"text":"And the truth is, this is a human problem."},{"time":481474,"text":"We're all, under certain\ncircumstances, willfully blind."},{"time":487839,"text":"What the research shows\nis that some people are blind"},{"time":490387,"text":"out of fear. They're\nafraid of retaliation."},{"time":493992,"text":"And some people are blind\nbecause they think, well,"},{"time":497367,"text":"seeing anything is just futile."},{"time":499785,"text":"Nothing's ever going to change."},{"time":501641,"text":"If we make a protest, if we protest\nagainst the Iraq War,"},{"time":504455,"text":"nothing changes, so why bother?"},{"time":506225,"text":"Better not to see this stuff at all."},{"time":510767,"text":"And the recurrent theme\nthat I encounter all the time"},{"time":513765,"text":"is people say, \"Well, you know,"},{"time":516245,"text":"the people who do see,\nthey're whistleblowers,"},{"time":519745,"text":"and we all know what happens to them.\""},{"time":522369,"text":"So there's this profound\nmythology around whistleblowers"},{"time":526418,"text":"which says, first of all,\nthey're all crazy."},{"time":530731,"text":"But what I've found going around the world"},{"time":533044,"text":"and talking to whistleblowers\nis, actually,"},{"time":536231,"text":"they're very loyal and quite\noften very conservative people."},{"time":540986,"text":"They're hugely dedicated\nto the institutions that they work for,"},{"time":544891,"text":"and the reason that they speak up,"},{"time":547198,"text":"the reason they insist on seeing,"},{"time":550080,"text":"is because they care so\nmuch about the institution"},{"time":553577,"text":"and want to keep it healthy."},{"time":557163,"text":"And the other thing that people often say"},{"time":559326,"text":"about whistleblowers is,\n\"Well, there's no point,"},{"time":562554,"text":"because you see what happens to them."},{"time":565123,"text":"They are crushed."},{"time":566437,"text":"Nobody would want to go\nthrough something like that.\""},{"time":570179,"text":"And yet, when I talk to whistleblowers,"},{"time":573506,"text":"the recurrent tone that I hear is pride."},{"time":578666,"text":"I think of Joe Darby."},{"time":581051,"text":"We all remember the photographs\nof Abu Ghraib,"},{"time":584503,"text":"which so shocked the world\nand showed the kind of war"},{"time":588225,"text":"that was being fought in Iraq."},{"time":590889,"text":"But I wonder who remembers Joe Darby,"},{"time":593900,"text":"the very obedient, good soldier"},{"time":597396,"text":"who found those photographs\nand handed them in."},{"time":602159,"text":"And he said, \"You know,\nI'm not the kind of guy"},{"time":605877,"text":"to rat people out, but some things\njust cross the line."},{"time":610103,"text":"Ignorance is bliss, they say,"},{"time":612199,"text":"but you can't put\nup with things like this.\""},{"time":615927,"text":"I talked to Steve Bolsin,\na British doctor,"},{"time":618962,"text":"who fought for five years\nto draw attention"},{"time":623268,"text":"to a dangerous surgeon\nwho was killing babies."},{"time":628291,"text":"And I asked him why\nhe did it, and he said,"},{"time":630363,"text":"\"Well, it was really my daughter\nwho prompted me to do it."},{"time":634449,"text":"She came up to me one night,\nand she just said,"},{"time":636713,"text":"'Dad, you can't let the kids die.'\""},{"time":640142,"text":"Or I think of Cynthia Thomas,"},{"time":642893,"text":"a really loyal army\ndaughter and army wife,"},{"time":646878,"text":"who, as she saw her friends and relations"},{"time":649830,"text":"coming back from the Iraq\nWar, was so shocked"},{"time":654132,"text":"by their mental condition"},{"time":656020,"text":"and the refusal of the military\nto recognize and acknowledge"},{"time":660051,"text":"post-traumatic stress syndrome"},{"time":662715,"text":"that she set up a cafe\nin the middle of a military town"},{"time":668323,"text":"to give them legal, psychological\nand medical assistance."},{"time":673953,"text":"And she said to me, she said,\n\"You know, Margaret,"},{"time":676893,"text":"I always used to say I didn't\nknow what I wanted to be"},{"time":680686,"text":"when I grow up."},{"time":682974,"text":"But I've found myself in this cause,"},{"time":687467,"text":"and I'll never be the same.\""},{"time":692484,"text":"We all enjoy so many freedoms today,"},{"time":695780,"text":"hard-won freedoms:"},{"time":697736,"text":"the freedom to write and publish\nwithout fear of censorship,"},{"time":701204,"text":"a freedom that wasn't here\nthe last time I came to Hungary;"},{"time":704979,"text":"a freedom to vote,\nwhich women in particular"},{"time":707465,"text":"had to fight so hard for;"},{"time":709944,"text":"the freedom for people of different\nethnicities and cultures"},{"time":712826,"text":"and sexual orientation to live\nthe way that they want."},{"time":717782,"text":"But freedom doesn't exist\nif you don't use it,"},{"time":722616,"text":"and what whistleblowers do,"},{"time":724957,"text":"and what people like Gayla Benefield do"},{"time":727524,"text":"is they use the freedom that they have."},{"time":732130,"text":"And what they're very\nprepared to do is recognize"},{"time":735612,"text":"that yes, this is going to be an argument,"},{"time":738242,"text":"and yes I'm going to have a lot of rows"},{"time":741234,"text":"with my neighbors\nand my colleagues and my friends,"},{"time":745223,"text":"but I'm going to become\nvery good at this conflict."},{"time":748445,"text":"I'm going to take on the naysayers,"},{"time":750788,"text":"because they'll make my argument\nbetter and stronger."},{"time":755708,"text":"I can collaborate with my opponents"},{"time":758140,"text":"to become better at what I do."},{"time":762622,"text":"These are people of immense persistence,"},{"time":765444,"text":"incredible patience,\nand an absolute determination"},{"time":770347,"text":"not to be blind and not to be silent."},{"time":775818,"text":"When I went to Libby, Montana,"},{"time":779011,"text":"I visited the asbestosis clinic"},{"time":782372,"text":"that Gayla Benefield brought into being,"},{"time":786293,"text":"a place where at first some of the people"},{"time":789173,"text":"who wanted help and needed\nmedical attention"},{"time":792415,"text":"went in the back door"},{"time":795045,"text":"because they didn't want to acknowledge"},{"time":797530,"text":"that she'd been right."},{"time":799975,"text":"I sat in a diner, and I watched"},{"time":803148,"text":"as trucks drove up and down the highway,"},{"time":807176,"text":"carting away the earth out of gardens"},{"time":811430,"text":"and replacing it with fresh,\nuncontaminated soil."},{"time":818342,"text":"I took my 12-year-old daughter with me,"},{"time":820602,"text":"because I really wanted her to meet Gayla."},{"time":823989,"text":"And she said, \"Why? What's the big deal?\""},{"time":826905,"text":"I said, \"She's not a movie star,"},{"time":829090,"text":"and she's not a celebrity,\nand she's not an expert,"},{"time":833377,"text":"and Gayla's the first person who'd say"},{"time":836115,"text":"she's not a saint."},{"time":839059,"text":"The really important thing about Gayla"},{"time":842199,"text":"is she is ordinary."},{"time":844866,"text":"She's like you, and she's like me."},{"time":849692,"text":"She had freedom,\nand she was ready to use it.\""},{"time":855655,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":857154,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}